markdown.markdownText:
**RUM (REAL USER MONITORING)**

Coralogix's Real User Monitoring (RUM) is an advanced monitoring solution that provides unparalleled visibility into your application's frontend performance, all from the perspective of real users in real time. With RUM, you can gain a comprehensive understanding of how your application performs across a variety of browsers, devices, and networks, allowing you to quickly detect issues that might be affecting your users' experience.

This dashboard is part of out-of-the-box RUM extension, providing real-time visibility into application's frontend performance.

**Use Cases Covered**

* Session Overview
* Page Performance
* Web Vitals 
* Session Errors
* Network Request Context
* Resource Timing

More about  RUM [here](https://coralogix.com/docs/user-guides/rum/getting-started/real-user-monitoring/).

markdown.markdownText: ```Core Web Vitals - Core Web Vitals is a set of specific page experience metrics identified by Google as essential for providing a good user experience. These metrics focus on web page loading, interactivity, and visual stability aspects.  ```

widgets.title: Largest Contentful Paint (LCP)
widgets.description: LCP measures the time it takes for the largest piece of content, such as an image or text block, to become visible to the user. It indicates how quickly the main content of the page loads.

source logs 
| filter $p.subsystemName.arrayContains($l.subsystemname)

widgets.title: First Input Delay (FID)
widgets.description: FID measures the time delay between a user's first interaction, such as clicking a button or tapping a link, and the browser's response. It reflects the interactivity of a web page and measures how quickly users can interact with the page.

widgets.title: Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS)
widgets.description: CLS measures the number of unexpected layout shifts that occur during the loading of a web page. It quantifies the visual stability of a page by tracking elements that move or shift position, potentially causing a frustrating experience for users.

dataprimeQuery.text:
source logs 
| filter $p.subsystemName.arrayContains($l.subsystemname)
| filter $p.app_name == null || $p.app_name.arrayContains(cx_rum.version_metadata.app_name)
| filter $p.device == null || $p.device.arrayContains(cx_rum.session_context.device) 
| filter $p.country_name == null || $p.country_name.arrayContains(cx_rum.session_context.ip_geoip.country_name)   
| filter $p.app_version == null ||  $p.app_version.arrayContains(cx_rum.version_metadata.app_version)
| filter $p.browser == null ||  $p.browser.arrayContains(cx_rum.session_context.browser)
| filter $p.session_id == null || $p.session_id.arrayContains(cx_rum.session_context.session_id)
| filter cx_rum.web_vitals_context.name == 'CLS'
| agg percentile(0.75, $d.cx_rum.web_vitals_context.value) as CLS
| create CLS from case {CLS==null->0,_->CLS}
